## üõ†Ô∏è Initial Setup (One-Time)

### Prerequisites

These commands were used to set up the development environment from scratch:

```bash
# 1. Install Node.js (includes npm and npx)
brew install node

# Verify installation
node --version  # v25.1.0
npm --version   # 11.6.2
npx --version   # 11.6.2
```

### Create Next.js Project

```bash
# Navigate to your workspace
cd /Users/robertdelacruz/Personal_Website

# Create Next.js app with TypeScript, ESLint, Tailwind, App Router
npx create-next-app@latest robertdelacruz.com \
  --typescript \
  --eslint \
  --tailwind \
  --app \
  --src-dir \
  --import-alias "@/*"

# Configuration choices made:
# - TypeScript: Yes
# - ESLint: Yes
# - Tailwind CSS: Yes
# - App Router: Yes
# - src/ directory: Yes
# - Import alias (@/*): Yes (default)
# - Turbopack: Yes (for faster dev server)
```

### Optional: Install pnpm (Faster Alternative to npm)

```bash
# Install pnpm globally
npm install -g pnpm

# Remove npm files and reinstall with pnpm
cd robertdelacruz.com
rm -rf node_modules package-lock.json
pnpm install

# Use pnpm commands going forward:
# pnpm dev, pnpm build, pnpm start, etc.
```

